quran[30]{c,v,t}:
  7,1,Alif-L√£m-Mƒ©m-бєҐ√£d
  7,2,"ЋєThis isЋЇ a Book sent down to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇвАФdo not let anxiety into your heart regarding itвАФso with it you may warn Ћєthe disbelieversЋЇ, and as a reminder to the believers"
  7,3,"Follow what has been sent down to you from your Lord, and do not take others as guardians besides Him. How seldom are you mindful"
  7,4,ЋєImagineЋЇ how many societies We have destroyed! Our torment took them by surprise Ћєwhile sleepingЋЇ at night or midday
  7,5,"Their only cryвАФwhen overwhelmed by Our tormentвАФwas, вАЬWe have indeed been wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  7,6,We will surely question those who received messengers and We will question the messengers ЋєthemselvesЋЇ
  7,7,Then We will give them a full account with sure knowledgeвАФfor We were never absent
  7,8,"The weighing on that Day will be just. As for those whose scale will be heavy Ћєwith good deedsЋЇ, ЋєonlyЋЇ they will be successful"
  7,9,"But those whose scale is light, they have doomed themselves for wrongfully denying Our signs"
  7,10,We have indeed established you on earth and provided you with a means of livelihood. ЋєYetЋЇ you seldom give any thanks
  7,11,"Surely We created you,¬†then shaped you, then said to the angels, вАЬProstrate before Adam,вАЭ so they all didвАФbut not Ibl√Ѓs,¬†who refused to prostrate with the others"
  7,12,"Allah asked, вАЬWhat prevented you from prostrating when I commanded you?вАЭ He replied, вАЬI am better than he is: You created me from fire and him from clay.вАЭ"
  7,13,"Allah said, вАЬThen get down from Paradise! It is not for you to be arrogant here. So get out! You are truly one of the disgraced.вАЭ"
  7,14,"He appealed, вАЬThen delay my end until the Day of their resurrection.вАЭ"
  7,15,"Allah said, вАЬYou are delayed Ћєuntil the appointed DayЋЇ.вАЭ"
  7,16,"He said, вАЬFor leaving me to stray I will lie in ambush for them on Your Straight Path"
  7,17,"I will approach them from their front, their back, their right, their left, and then You will find most of them ungrateful.вАЭ"
  7,18,"Allah said, вАЬGet out of Paradise! You are disgraced and rejected! I will certainly fill up Hell with you and your followers all together.вАЭ"
  7,19,"ЋєAllah said,ЋЇ вАЬO Adam! Live with your wife in Paradise and eat from wherever you please, but do not approach this tree, or else you will be wrongdoers.вАЭ"
  7,20,"Then Satan tempted them in order to expose what was hidden of their nakedness. He said, вАЬYour Lord has forbidden this tree to you only to prevent you from becoming angels or immortals.вАЭ"
  7,21,"And he swore to them, вАЬI am truly your sincere advisor.вАЭ"
  7,22,"So he brought about their fall through deception. And when they tasted of the tree, their nakedness was exposed to them, prompting them to cover themselves with leaves from Paradise. Then their Lord called out to them, вАЬDid I not forbid you from that tree and Ћєdid I notЋЇ tell you that Satan is your sworn enemy?вАЭ"
  7,23,"They replied, вАЬOur Lord! We have wronged ourselves. If You do not forgive us and have mercy on us, we will certainly be losers.вАЭ"
  7,24,"Allah said, вАЬDescend as enemies to each other.¬†You will find in the earth a residence and provision for your appointed stay.вАЭ"
  7,25,"He added, вАЬThere you will live, there you will die, and from there you will be resurrected.вАЭ"
  7,26,"O children of Adam! We have provided for you clothing to cover your nakedness and as an adornment. However, the best clothing is righteousness. This is one of AllahвАЩs bounties, so perhaps you will be mindful"
  7,27,O children of Adam! Do not let Satan deceive you as he tempted your parents out of Paradise and caused their cover to be removed in order to expose their nakedness. Surely he and his soldiers watch you from where you cannot see them. We have made the devils allies of those who disbelieve
  7,28,"Whenever they commit a shameful deed,¬†they say, вАЬWe found our forefathers doing it and Allah has commanded us to do it.вАЭ Say, вАЬNo! Allah never commands what is shameful. How can you attribute to Allah what you do not know?вАЭ"
  7,29,"Say, ЋєO Prophet,ЋЇ вАЬMy Lord has commanded uprightness and dedication Ћєto Him aloneЋЇ in worship, calling upon Him with sincere devotion. Just as He first brought you into being, you will be brought to life again.вАЭ"
  7,30,"He has guided some, while others are destined to stray. They have taken devils as their masters instead of AllahвАФthinking they are ЋєrightlyЋЇ guided"